This paper discusses experiments conducted to improve a job title classification system using semantic representation strategies. The paper focuses on natural language processing techniques such as word embeddings and document similarity measures, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image classification techniques, which are relevant to the sub-field of computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL and cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
